Let us consider whether, if indeed Jesus still live and be with us, we have any reason for so radical a failure of belief in him as the Church has always shown, affirming that he does not abide by his own simple words and lead each soul into fullest life, without outward conformity one to another, or the supre- macy of the doctrinaires. Undoubtedly dogma is needful‚ and its profoundest study‚ as also large conformity‚ as a matter of convenience3 at the same time it is certain that either God in the human personality of the Shepherd King has direct dealings with each of us, or the Church's greatest tenets are false.
